[Notify & Handlers]
It is exactly the same as a Task, but it will run when called by another Task.

[pre_tasks and post_tasks]
It run certain tasks before or after running the main tasks, roles.
● pre_tasks
The pre_tasks means before execution of below tasks, roles, post_tasks. 
In a playbook will cause those tasks to run before all other tasks, including roles.
● post_tasks
The post_tasks means after execution of above all pre_tasks, tasks, roles. 
In a playbook will cause those tasks to run after all others tasks, including roles.
